thought1_dissim_self_general_1: I don't quite enjoy people who are too too different from me. I tend to get along better with people who are as energetic and outgoing.
thought2_dissim_self_general_1: I would want to give them a chance though, because people can pleasantly surprise you. Sometimes, hanging with people not too similar can be better to decrease competition.
thought1_dissim_other_general_1: It's hard to say because I don't know the traits of this personality, but either they'll enjoy it because they enjoy differences or they'll hate it because they prefer similarities.
thought2_dissim_other_general_1: I infer that 4 seems to be the most outgoing and energetic, and usually humans like those traits, so I feel like they may enjoy the conversation, especially since 4 may be the type to add fun to the conversation. I could be assuming though so I don't know.
thought1_sim_self_general_1: I would feel like there would be energy, fun, and spontaneity. I think we will bounce off each other and get excited by the similarities.
thought2_sim_self_general_1: If we're too similar but different in the wrong ways, it can be a breeding ground of competition. Who's the loudest, who's the most fun, who has the most energy.
thought1_sim_other_general_1: I assume they would enjoy talking to someone similar to them. Sometimes it can be exhausting being the only excited and outgoing one, so this might help them feel less conscious of their actions. Sometimes if I'm the only outgoing, I overthink if I'm doing too much or embarrassing myself. It would be nice to have someone match energy.
thought2_sim_other_general_1: They might expect us to have similar beliefs because we have similar personalities. However, many people can have this personality type and still be completely different, due to race, culture, background, beliefs, etc.
thought1_dissim_self_race_1: They probably won't be able to relate or understand certain issues I face in society, my humor, certain stuff.
thought2_dissim_self_race_1: If they try too hard to copy my slang, jokes, style, etc. I'm going to think they're weird and trying to appropriate my race.
thought1_dissim_other_race_1: I think most people prefer people who are similar to them, so they may have a polite thought but also might walk on eggshells because my race is honestly the most marginalized in America.
thought2_dissim_other_race_1: They might be interested in getting to know more about my culture and beliefs, especially if they enjoy diversity and civil rights.
thought1_sim_self_race_1: They would most likely want to be friends because we could understand each other's style, experiences, humor. We probably have been treated similarly in this setting.

thought1_dissim_self_general_1: Well since we have different personalities, I would first try to get to know this person slightly better, maybe through some basic questions to better understand how this person thinks and acts.
thought2_dissim_self_general_1: I think after that, we can just continue our conversations based on the answers and emotions to the first few questions. I would say I am a pretty outgoing person, so I can talk to most people regardless of their personality or interest, it would just have to be a judgement call as to what to talk about.
thought1_dissim_other_general_1: Well if they are a bit less extroverted, they might think that I am extremely talkative and outgoing, which I think is a good thing - this is what I want people to think of me anyway.
thought2_dissim_other_general_1: If they realize that they have a similar personality to me, or at the very least have some similar interests etc, they might find it easy to talk to me and get to know me better. (or rather, they would want to know me better).
thought1_sim_self_general_1: Well I know that this person has the same outgoing personality as me, so I think that I would want to see what they are interested in - often times people with similar personalities have similar interests.
thought2_sim_self_general_1: I would also want to hear some of their thoughts on general topics, especially since they seem like they would be the type of people that I could have conversations with about most topics.
thought1_sim_other_general_1: They would think similarly to me, and hopefully see me as someone that is very similar in personality to them which could allow them to think of me as a friend or someone they can talk to.
thought2_sim_other_general_1: Along the same lines, they might be interested in knowing some of my interests and goals because it might align with theirs.
thought1_dissim_self_race_1: I don't think that this has any effect on how much or how little I want to get to know someone, it is all the same to me.
thought2_dissim_self_race_1: The only thing I could think of is someone with a different race might not have the same shared experiences as someone of my race - this doesn't mean we can't share other things which is why I think that I would have no difference in anticipation.
thought1_dissim_other_race_1: I think that if they had the same personality as me, they wouldn't think twice about wanting to get to know me better.
thought2_dissim_other_race_1: I think that they recognize the same thing as me - they won't necessarily have the same upbringing as me, so maybe less to talk about on that front, but there are always things that we can connect on.
thought1_sim_self_race_1: Now when I see this, I can assume that they might have had similar experiences to me, and they share similar upbringings etc.
thought2_sim_self_race_1: My mind is now able to really connect with this person on a slightly deeper level by leveraging the shared experiences we both might have.
thought1_sim_other_race_1: Similarly, I think that they might be more open to having a longer conversation and talking about how we live.
thought2_sim_other_race_1: Also it might allow them to think of more things on the spot to connect on (where are you from initially etc.) which can help someone that is more introverted open up slightly.

thought2_dissim_self_general_2: However, I think that they might be a bit more introverted etc so that could mean I would have to ask questions etc.

thought2_dissim_other_general_2: However, they might be interested in getting to know someone new that isn't similar to them.

thought1_dissim_self_general_1: Since the have a different personality than me, I want to bemaking sure to keep track of what I am saying so that I don't accidently offend them.
thought2_dissim_self_general_1: I think I would let them talk first so that they feel comfortable talking about what the know, and this way, I can also restrict myself to talking about things they find interesting or not upsetting.
thought1_dissim_other_general_1: I would think that they also upon seeing we have different personality types would want to cater to my interests. even subconciously.
thought2_dissim_other_general_1: They might also be worried that with different personality types, we are not as compatible and thus less likely to become anything more than acquaintances.
thought1_sim_self_general_1: Since we are the same personality type, I think we would have more things in common, allowing us to have a longer, more natural conversation because we likely share similar interests.
thought2_sim_self_general_1: There is less of a feeling of needing to control what I say, and instead, more of a desire to say many things in order to have a conversation with someone who thinks the way I do.
thought1_sim_other_general_1: I think they would think the same of feeling like they can talk about anything without fear of offending the other person (me). If we share the same personality type, we most likely also share the same interests and opinions on them, so the conversation could flow easier.
thought2_sim_other_general_1: They might feel like they can talk first because they don't need to gage how I feel on certain issues, or they may feel comfortable in talking about things a bit more controversial.
thought1_dissim_self_race_1: Having a different race means that despite potentially having a similar personality type, we don't have many shared experiences, which can make the conversation a little harder to strike, as now we have a more limited knowledge to discuss from.
thought2_dissim_self_race_1: I would worry that by being Asian, I could be assumed to act a certain way or be a certain way by my conversation partner, making me more conscious of what I am saying.
thought1_dissim_other_race_1: I think they would also think that talking to an Asian could be difficult because there is a lack of familiarity.
thought2_dissim_other_race_1: They might think they can't share unique things about themselves because I might not understand them.
thought1_sim_self_race_1: With a shared familiarity, the conversation flows easier.
thought2_sim_self_race_1: They have a greater base of knowledge to talk from, so it is easier to converse.
thought1_sim_other_race_1: They most likely feel more comfortable discussing more unknown things because I might know them.
thought2_sim_other_race_1: Since they are talking to a fellow Asian, they are celebrating their ethnicity and race.
thought1_dissim_self_general_2: I would want to make sure that I am making them feel comfortable since we might not mesh as well together.
thought2_dissim_self_general_2: I would feel a little more nervous because I don't want to say anything that could offend them, but I have less knowledge of their opinions and how they would react because they have a different personality type.
thought1_dissim_other_general_2: I think they might feel a little worried as well that they might not connect as well with me because of having a different personality type.
thought2_dissim_other_general_2: I think they might think to be a little more careful of how/what they speak so as not to be too polarizing.
thought1_sim_self_general_2: Since they have the same personality type as me, I don't have to think as much about what I am saying.
thought2_sim_self_general_2: I think I would feel like I can be more talkative because I have a smaller chance of offending them.
thought1_sim_other_general_2: I think they might think they can talk more freely and about anything since I am likely to have the same opinions.
thought2_sim_other_general_2: I think they might think to bring up topics they rarely do with people in the fear that it may be unappealing.
thought1_dissim_self_race_2: I think I would feel like I can't talk as freely about my ethnicity because they might not understand it.
thought2_dissim_self_race_2: I think I might feel a little more wary because they might judge me on stereotypes solely because of my race.
thought1_dissim_other_race_2: I think they might think to stick to conventional and surface level topics that anyone can chat about.
thought2_dissim_other_race_2: I think they might believe that they should be more careful of saying things because they don't know how I will react.
thought1_sim_self_race_2: I can talk to them openly about experiences that are specific to people from my race.
thought2_sim_self_race_2: I think that I would want to say more things that gets them to be my friend, especially because I prioritize making friends from my race and ethnicity.
thought1_sim_other_race_2: I think I would feel like I can talk about experiences that are specific to my race/ethnicity.
thought2_sim_other_race_2: I think I would think that I want to be friends with them more because I value having friends of the same race and ethnicity.

thought1_dissim_other_race_1: I feel like they still might not want to talk to me because we're of a different race. There will always be that stigma that it is far more comfortable to interact with someone of your own background than it is someone of a completely different race.
thought2_dissim_other_race_1: It is 2024, so they might not have those thoughts and may be way more open to meeting people of another race.
thought1_sim_self_race_1: I would be excited to talk to my partner regardless of their race. Just because I like meeting people and my hopes would be that they would reciprocate that energy so that we can have a good conversation.
thought2_sim_self_race_1: I would be even more excited because I always love meeting people who have mixed backgrounds like I do or a combination of my mix (Filipino-Mexican). I feel like it's fun to share some aspects of the same culture and overlapping childhood memories make it easier to connect.
thought1_sim_other_race_1: I would hope that they are excited to meet me because we have the same background and can connect easily by bonding over jokes and shared experiences about our cultures.
thought2_sim_other_race_1: I also know that there are some people within my same race that can be really racist to our own people, so they might not want to talk to me or be as interested in getting to know me as a person. It also depends on the definition of the term "race." If "race," means Asians in general, I feel like there is a stigma among Southeast Asians against associating with South Asians like myself. At least in my experience, Southeast Asians can be very cliquey and not want to interact with those who are a different kind of Asian.
thought1_dissim_self_general_2: I'm excited to learn more about what makes them tick as people. I love learning people's stories and why they are who they are.
thought2_dissim_self_general_2: I want to know them better so that I can better understand and interact with people of different personality types.
thought1_dissim_other_general_2: I would hope that they are generally interested in getting to know someone else. However, since they think differently than me, I have no way of truely knowing how they think.
thought2_dissim_other_general_2: I think they might still be a little apprehensive of someone like me, given they have a different personality than me. They might not want to talk to someone so energetic or might think I'm too nerdy or otherwise not cool.
thought1_sim_self_general_2: I am very excited at the idea of getting to know someone who is like me. I feel like I could get along really well with them given that we have similar ways of approaching the world.
thought2_sim_self_general_2: I feel like it's a lot less pressure talking to someone who I know thinks the way that I think. I don't have to worry as much about trying to make a good impression since I already know that they wouldn't really care (since I don't care).

thought1_dissim_self_general_1: The first thought that would come to mind in anticipation for talking with my conversation partner would be to determine what values or inherent characteristics made this person achieve a different personality than me?
thought2_dissim_self_general_1: The second thought that would come to mind in anticipation for talking with my conversation partner would be to understand how open they seem to get to know me or even to just have a friendly conversation together, given the fact that we were assigned different personality types.
thought1_dissim_other_general_1: In anticipation of talking to me, I think my conversation partner's first thought would be something along the lines of why was I paired with this person specifically and what about my personality or unique characteristics makes me different from them?
thought2_dissim_other_general_1: In anticipation of talking to me, I think my conversation partner's second thought would be something along the lines of what interests or personal habits does my partner convey which might be related to the fact that we were assigned different personality types?
thought1_sim_self_general_1: The first thought that would come to mind would be to determine how or why did both of us land within the same personality type. Furthermore, seeing how this can be correlated to our personal habits and unique characteristics.
thought2_sim_self_general_1: The second thought that would come to mind would be to determine or maybe even anticipate how likely we would be able to get along well with each other, given the fact that we both were identified under the same personality type. This connects to the mundane societal idea that "opposites attract" in relationships, but what if this situation proves to be an exception of this inherent belief?
thought1_sim_other_general_1: The first thought that my conversation partner might have in mind would probably be something related to how or why we ended up achieving the same personality type, and how our personal attributes, characteristics, or even unique qualities that shape who we are had an influence in our personality type assignments.
thought2_sim_other_general_1: The second thought that my conversation partner might have in mind might be to figure out what about ourselves, aside from our particular personality type, can we find a connection between. For example, maybe through conversation we can find that we attend the same school, are in the same graduating class, maybe even share some extracurricular assessments.
thought1_dissim_self_race_1: The first thought that comes to mind would be to learn more about their culture, given the fact that society oftentimes ties this notion of race to having and experiencing a different culture and even growing up with different values
thought2_dissim_self_race_1: The second thought that comes to mind would be to understand how their upbringing in a different culture is connected to their personality now and how they portray and carry themselves on a daily basis
thought1_dissim_other_race_1: The first thought that might come to mind is to understand how the partner in this scenario has different familial values or cultural values growing up in a different family environment
thought2_dissim_other_race_1: The second thought that might come to mind is to understand how growing up in a different cultural upbringing influences my current day-to-day life experiences and how I view the world
thought1_sim_self_race_1: My first thought would be to talk through some of the general similarities within our familial upbringings to identify if we have some similar cultural points
thought2_sim_self_race_1: My second thought would be to identify how our particular family upbringings would now contribute to our perspective on the world, and noticing any interesting similarities or even any differences between our opinions
thought1_sim_other_race_1: The first thought that might come to mind is to identify how our upbringings may have had some similarities in regards to cultural exposure or even identifiying any family values that are the same
thought2_sim_other_race_1: The second thought that might come to mind is to identify which, if any, perspectives on life we have similar opinions of, and how our personal upbringings in our homes are a reflection of that.

thought2_dissim_self_general_2: The second thought that come to mind is to talk about our future spring break plans

thought2_dissim_other_general_2: The second thought that might come to mind is learning if we have any interesting spring break plans

thought1_dissim_self_general_1: I imagine them having a very on-the-go mentality, likely with scattered eye contact. Maybe they anticipate going somewhere after the conversation and will make it clear in their body language
thought2_dissim_self_general_1: I also think that they'll be very outgoing and enunciate their body movements; this could in turn be a bit overstimulating
thought1_dissim_other_general_1: They could be excited to talk about themselves, as I'll continuously follow up and dig deeper if they say something interesting.
thought2_dissim_other_general_1: They could also be a bit bored due to my habit of engaging in small talk; I tend to ask very basic questions (almost like an interview) with people I do not know well. This could be something like "do you know X person" or "what are you doing for spring break".
thought1_sim_self_general_1: They might be a bit shy. I think that they'll await for someone else, like myself, to initiate the conversation.
thought2_sim_self_general_1: They'll be pre-professional or very achievement focus. Maybe instead of focusing on social life, they'll prioritize talking about academics/career.

thought1_dissim_self_general_1: I want to know what differentiates us in our opinions but also ways of communicating and building relationships.  I would be mindful of their body language, ways of speaking, and general level of enthusiasm in our conversation.
thought2_dissim_self_general_1: I would want to push them to see how different we truly are or if the differences are relatively inconsequential.  For example, if I start picking up signs that we have a disagreement, I would push them to see if they become angry, reserved, defensive, or accepting of my disagreement.  Essentially, I would want want to qualify our differences.
thought1_dissim_other_general_1: I would hope they would think it was interesting how we are different and want to know what our differences are.  They might ask me what hobbies I have or activities I pursue.
thought2_dissim_other_general_1: Maybe they might also try to force similarities to bridge the gap between us.  When talking and getting to know each other, they might move on from topics where we don't relate to topics that we do.  This would allow us to find meaning in our conversation and grow from strangers to acquaintances.
thought1_sim_self_general_1: I would first want to test if we truly are similar in personality.  I feel like personality types are incredibly subjective and can come across in many different ways so even if we have similar personality types, we still could be opposite individuals.  Essentially, I would be very skeptical initially.
thought2_sim_self_general_1: I would want to ask about situations they have experienced and see how alike we are.  Also, I would be curious about their upbringing.

thought1_dissim_self_general_1: Is this person more extroverted or introverted? I'd like to know whether I am going to be the one triggering most of the interactions in the conversation, or if I can take a more backseat approach. Understanding whether this person is an introvert or extrovert will also allow me to understand what they might be passionate about, or where their interests may lie.
thought2_dissim_self_general_1: How do I match this person's energy/vibe? I find it easy to get along with most of the people that I meet because I match their energy. I reflect back what is necessary to make the conversation flow or comfortable for both of us.
thought1_dissim_other_general_1: Is this person very different from me? This is a likely question since the only information we'll have about each other is that our personalities are apparently different. I think the person will likely be anticipating what exactly differs between us two.
thought2_dissim_other_general_1: Nervousness or trepidation. I think it's natural to feel some light nervousness when being launched into a conversation, especially if you know the other person will be different from you. Some people might worry about the awkwardness of the interaction or lack of mutual connection in terms of personalities.
thought1_sim_self_general_1: What makes this person similar to me? I would be curious to see which traits that I know I have are evident in the other person. I would be interested to see how our similarities have manifested in behaviors/activities throughout our differentiated lives.
thought2_sim_self_general_1: Will I dislike this person? I get the feeling that I might not like someone who's super similar to me because my subconscious could perceive them as a threat. I could also see myself really liking this person because I can understand them.
thought1_sim_other_general_1: Why is this person similar to me? I think this will be a common question for everyone involved.
thought2_sim_other_general_1: What makes this person different from me? Maybe this person is wondering about whether personality makes a person more similar to someone, or if stuff like upbringing or background is more important.
thought1_dissim_self_race_1: What interests will we have in common? We might have a similar background in terms of people that we hung out around, our parents' parenting style, etc.
